<subSubSection pageId="94" pageNumber="694" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="94.[171,1377,2101,2922]" pageId="94" pageNumber="694">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[171,404,2574,2608]" pageId="94" pageNumber="694">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
The Long-tailed Talaud Mosaic-tailed Ratis thought to be more arboreal than the sympatric Short-tailed Talaud Mosaic-tailed Rat. These two species both have the relatively short feet typical of climbing species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[172,1111,2692,2726]" pageId="94" pageNumber="694" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="94.[171,1377,2101,2922]" box="[172,1111,2692,2726]" pageId="94" pageNumber="694">
